Title: I Wade out into Other Forms
Description: June 23
---
It used to come and go as it wanted, it seemed, love. It left me feeling
 helpless.
I wondered if there might be some kind of leash I could slip around its neck to
 remedy that situation, cherishing certain emotions as I did. Not wanting them
 to wander off.
An idea occurred to meï¼š to hold God accountable when He said, In my image I
 have made you.
I demanded to see that, I started to picket His house, to see more of myself.
Waves of Him now greet my shore. I wade out into other forms of myself. And I
 swim in what I never thought I could.
Inseparate is any creature or object from Light, from the Ocean, became my
 discovery.
